  "notes": "một = “one.” It’s the number 1, but it also works like “a / an” in English.\n\nYou use một + classifier + noun when counting things.  \n\nIt can also mean “one single” for emphasis (một mình = alone, by oneself). In casual speech, it sometimes softens meaning like “a bit” (một chút = a little).\n\nStrong contrast to remember: một (one) vs hai (two).",
